5:
Oh no, oh no, oh noooo... Captain,
can't this thing go any faster?!
7:
This ol' girl's trying her best already,
okay! The engines are on full blast!
10:
Those fellows are surprisingly
persistent, to chase us this far...
14:
Hahaha! Without Marina around,
these Crimson Blades are easy
pickings!
26: This isn't good... He needs first aid!
28:
Attention: this medical service
vessel is approaching your location.
Please cease all combat
immediately.
36:
We are the Fellowship of Floof, and
we offer medical care to all. We are
en route to provide assistance.
Please hold your fire. This is your last
warning.
38:
...I don't think they're going to listen,
Captain.
41:
It appears there's an injured man on
the smaller vessel.
44:
I'll stop the pirates' cannon fire first.
Please cover me.
47:
Captain, wait! Argh... There he goes
again!
49:
All hands, prepare to fire! We're
covering the captain!
53:
I dunno who the hell these guys are,
but they're starting to get on my
nerves! Sink 'em!
62:
I have a patient waiting for me, so
let's make this quick.
64:
Don't worry, I won't do any
permanent damage. I'm a doctor,
not a soldier.
69:
Oh, you're gonna regret comin'
here... GET HIM, MEN!
73:
Whoa... Did he really just do that
alone?
82:
You've got an injured person on
board, right? Let me see him.
85: Who in the world are you?
90:
I'm Liao, captain of the Fellowship of
Fluff, a crew that provides medical
treatment to any and all who need
it. I'm also a doctor... Meow.
93:
Come join me on my ship. We can
talk more there.
104:
His wounds aren't deep. He should
wake soon.
108: We are in your debt, Liao.
111:
I'm curious though. Why did you
treat the pirates as well?
114:
Everyone deserves to be treated
equally. That's the way we
operatethe ideal that our captain
aims for.
117:
Doctors have a responsibility to take
care of everyone, regardless of their
moral character.
119:
To shirk that responsibility would
mean our oceans will never be free
of pain and suffering.
123:
Treat equally, my ass! You're the one
who clobbered us!
127:
We warned to you stop firing. You
only have yourself to blame for
ignoring said warning.
129: By the way, this is your bill.
134:
Wh-what kinda sick joke is this?! You
think we have this much money lyin'
around?
138:
We also take payment in the form of
labor. You can get to work as soon
as you're healed.
141:
Just remember our most important
ruleall members of the Fellowship
of Floof are required to wear fluffy
ears.
155:
If that's the case, allow us to thank
you with payment as well...
158:
Ah, that's okay. We generally don't
bill victims of pirate attacks.
160:
That... doesn't sound like a very
feasible way of making a living.
164:
If we didn't have generous souls
donating to us, we would've had to
hang up our sails ages ago.
168:
...Even without them, I would've
persevered. I will never give up on
making my ideal a reality.
171:
As you can see, he's not letting
anything stop him, which is exactly
why the rest of us can't help but
follow along.
174:
You know, I'm feeling a little inspired
now too. Got any chores or cleaning
you need help with?
177:
...Eager to lend your aid, huh?
Sounds like you're one of us.
180: I should have fluffy ears that fit you.
183:
Guess there's no exceptions to that
rule...
189:
You're lower on supplies than I
expected.
192:
My first mate wasn't exaggerating.
We're always barely functioning with
what we have, especially when
we're out at sea.
196:
Liao, you mentioned donations
earlier... Are we allowed to
contribute as well?
202:
I almost can't believe what I'm
seeing. There truly is a way to travel
to different worlds... and it was with
the mermaids the whole time.
205:
With this, you should be able to
secure supplies from multiple
sources.
209:
Are there injured and ill people in
these other worlds?
213: Huh? I-I mean, yeah, but why...
217:
Understood. Then the Fellowship of
Floof shall set up a base of
operations here and further expand
our services.
222:
All right. Welcome to Starview
Village.
227:
I look forward to working with you
all... Meow.
232:
Err... Maybe I shouldn't ask this, but...
Why do you sometimes meow at
the end of your sentences?
236: It's cute. People like cute things, right?
